cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with scene categorization from images. The use of off-the-shelf pre-trained CNNs also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The study also involves the use of medial-axis based contour salience methods, which may place it in the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the comparison of CNN performance to human performance suggests that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
